      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the legal philosophy that the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of its text at the time it was adopted. Proponents argue this prevents judges from imposing their personal, ever-changing policy preferences onto the law. By adhering to original intent, originalism ensures that the Constitution remains a fixed, stable document reflecting the will of the founders. This approach is fundamentally about limiting judicial activism and respecting the democratic process.",
