      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The academic weight of the critique is substantial because it highlights the inherent difficulty in ever perfectly recovering the \"original intent\" of complex historical actors. Critics rightly point out that the framers were not a monolithic group, making any single \"original meaning\" debatable. Ultimately, the debate isn't just about change; it's a fundamental disagreement over whether the Constitution is a static document of historical agreement or a dynamic framework designed to evolve with the nation.",
      "source": "target",
